Fix some bugs in the MP4 header.,The sampling frequency and number of channels are stored several,times in the MP4 header. Some of them were hard coded (to 44.1kHz,and 2 channels),resulting in an invalid header.

Fixes the following issues (mainly for Samsung S3 on 4.1.2):,* On Samsung S3: reading an AAC file failed. A raw AAC stream starts with,2 bytes giving basic info about the stream (e.g. sampling frequency,,channel configuration). However if fed to the S3 decoder,MediaCodec will,crash. So now these two bytes are not fed to the encoder (MediaCodec has,already been configured and knows these parameters). This looks OK with,other devices too (e.g. Nexus 5 and 7 running Lollipop).,* On Samsung S3: AAC mono files are not decoded properly. The decoder,returns duplicated samples,as if the stream was stereo (maybe because,of the missing first 2 bytes...). This results is an audio stream with,a much lower pitch,containing half the data from the original stream,(Cf. length of the decoded stream is still the same as the original,not,twice). To solve that,the encoder now always encodes at least in stereo.,* Some device seem to fail encoding in AAC. I couldn't replicate the,issue with either my devices or several emulators. So now,until the root,cause is found,if the AAC encoding fails then the samples will be,exported in a WAVE file instead. (files will be much bigger than the .m4a,files,but ringtones are usually fairly small so it's should be fine).,* Make the AAC stream 2 frames (2048 samples) bigger than the original,stream: the encoder adds 2 empty frames (priming frames) before,processing the real data. As a result,the decoded samples contain,2 empty frames at the begining and are missing the last two frames. By,making the AAC file 2 frames bigger,the decoded samples will still,contain the 2 empty frames at the begining,but will at least contain,the end of the stream.

Started revising the class hierarchy,For this commit,I created a class called WaypointEnemy that IS-A,EnemyEntity. To test this new class,I changed class Hunter so that it,IS-A WaypointEnemy. I'm not sure whether to,make WaypointEnemy abstract,though. Part of me thinks it makes sense,but,part of me thinks it's an odd move,even though EnemyEntity is abstract. I,don't think this decision will be consequential,though.

Use newer API to decode/encode audio files; fix bugs and deprecated code.,Remove the CheapSoundFile classes and use newer APIs (16) instead to decode and,encode audio files using the hardware audio encoder/decoder directly.,This allows Ringdroid to decode more files (.ogg files for example),and get all,the samples instead of just one approximate value per frame. However it takes,longer to decode big audio files.,The new audio files created by the app will be encoded in MP4 (.m4a).,The MediaPlayer class is not used anymore to play the audio tracks. It is,replaced by a custom player based on AudioTrack.,Ringdroid won't use the device recording app anymore (not working on Nexus 5,running Lollipop for example). Instead it will record directly the audio using,the AudioRecord class.,This commit should fix all the major crashes (if not all),but has been tested,only on a Nexus 5 and a Nexus 7,and on Kit-Kat and Lollipop.,It also replaces all deprecated APIs with newer and valid ones.,In future commits:,* Update RingdroidEditActivity so that it uses the samples directly,instead,of just one coef per frame (even though Ringdroid has access to all the samples,now,it still generates one gain coefficient per "frame" in order not to change,the old code too much).,* Update RingdroidEditActivity to better handle gestures (smooth zoom in/out,for example instead of just 5 zoom levels).

Remove fake user agent string,only redirect on 301 response.,The reason for the user agent was that www.yelp.com would return a 303,"See Other" response directing to m.yelp.com when using the default user,agent string. In order to prevent this kind of redirect (because the,yelp app doesn't catch m.yelp.com for some reason) I faked a desktop,user agent.,This fix is to instead only respond to 301 "Moved Permanently",redirects,which is what short url redirectors use (though maybe not in,all cases...).,Also,the MultipleRedirectEvaluatorTask now recognizes a null return,string as indicating that no redirection was required,instead of,looking for a evaluation that doesn't change the url (which makes more,sense because urls that do not redirect return no 'location' in the http,header response).,Fixes #26.
